title: Former Arsenal youngster and ‘dench’ aficionado Emmanuel Frimpong moves to yet another club in Swedish first tier
text:
Click to share on Facebook (Opens in new window) Comments FORMER Arsenal youngster Emmanuel Frimpong has moved to yet another club – this time in the Swedish first tier. 
The midfielder and “dench” aficionado is onto his fourth club since leaving the Emirates in 2014 in the form of newly-promoted side AFC Eskilstuna. 3 Frimpong poses with the shirt of his new club AFC Eskilstuna in Sweden 
Keep up to date with ALL the Premier League news, gossip, transfers and goals on our club page plus fixtures, results and live match commentary 
It feels like a lifetime ago that the Ghana-born player was heralded as the next star of the future, having signed a two year deal after leaving Russian side Arsenal Tula. 
He was released after only three games by Tula, only signing for them last August from fellow Russian top flight club Ufa – after a move to MLS side Kansas Sporting City broke down. PA:Press Association 3 Emmanuel Frimpong played a handful of times for Arsenal but did not live up to his potential 
The free agent has been heralded as a marquee signing by the club formerly known as AFC United, ahead of the upcoming Allsvenskan season which kicks off in early April.

“This is a solicitation that means a lot to the club. It shows that we have the capacity to recruit this type of players to complement our squad for the season. 
The 25-year-old made 16 appearances in all competitions for the Gunners having come through their ranks – and had loans away at Wolves, Charlton and Fulham in the top flight. You know when you've been Frimponged 
Frimpong then moved briefly to Barnsley and did not ingratiate himself to Tykes fans as he posted on Instagram worried about his sex life, writing: "How am I gonna draw girls." 
He is perhaps more known for his foray into musoc, rapping a verse on his cousin Lethal Bizzle's 2012 hit "Leave It Yeah", with their "dench" catchphrase.
